sect1.sect2:
Introduction to cargo
Cargo is the Package Manager for Rust. Like that, during the build it uses curl to download cargo files which are actually .tar.gz source archives.
This package requires internet access to build and at runtime (when rust is compiling another package). It will use all available cores. It also needs the current or previous version to compile itself, so here a binary of the previous version is used to bootstrap.
&lfs80_checked;
Firefox will download a correctly named tarball, or you can download it via wget as:
wget https://github.com/rust-lang/cargo/archive/&cargo-version;.tar.gz \ -O cargo-&cargo-version;.tar.gz
